# Project rules — read and follow these on every task

## !! ANTI-STUB RULE — READ FIRST, APPLY ALWAYS !!

A task is ONLY complete when every method body contains WORKING Dart code.
The following patterns are FORBIDDEN outputs — they are stubs, not implementations:

```dart
// FORBIDDEN — stub with comment body
void tick(double dt) {
  // Tasks A and B are implemented here.
}

// FORBIDDEN — loop that does nothing
void handleOrders(List<Component> orders, double dt) {
  for (var order in orders) {
    if (order is PositionComponent) {
      // Handle movement logic here
    }
  }
}

// FORBIDDEN — empty callback
@override
Future<void> onTapDown(TapDownEvent event) async {
  // Handle vector tap
}
```

If you cannot implement a method body with real logic, ESCALATE (exit 2).
Do NOT write a stub and mark the task done. Stubs break future tasks silently.

Every task must have an observable result: something the player sees, or
something `flutter analyze` can verify. If there is no observable result,
you have not finished the task.

---

## What this project is

Astro Flux is a Flutter/Flame real-time strategy / idle game. Players capture
Stars, accumulate Motes, and fuse them into combat units to grow their force.
The full gameplay spec lives in `docs/unit_spec.md` — read it before any
gameplay task. The summary is below.

---

## Gameplay mechanics — authoritative summary (full spec: docs/unit_spec.md)

### Three unit tiers

| Tier | Name   | Speed (px/s) | Power | Max HP | Point value |
|------|--------|-------------|-------|--------|-------------|
| 1    | Mote   | 300         | 1     | 1      | 1           |
| 2    | Vector | 150         | 3     | 5      | 5           |
| 3    | Surge  | 60          | 9     | 25     | 25          |

### Selection — lasso drag
- Single-finger drag draws a selection rectangle on the canvas.
- All units whose world positions fall inside the rectangle are selected.
- A highlight ring renders around each selected unit.
- Tapping empty space with no drag clears the selection.

### Tap to move
- With units selected, tapping anywhere dispatches a MoveOrderEvent.
- Selected units march toward the tapped world position at their tier speed.
- Arriving at empty space: units idle at that position.
- Arriving at an enemy/neutral star: units contribute power and are consumed (see Stars).
- Arriving at a friendly star: units contribute power to upgrade it, then are consumed.
- Units engage enemy units automatically en route (see Combat).
- Selection clears after a move order is dispatched.

### Long-press to combine (≥ 600 ms)
- Long-pressing a selected group triggers a CombineOrderEvent.
- Each unit contributes its point value to a shared pool.
- If pool ≥ 25: spawn 1 Tier-3 Surge at group centroid, consume all selected units.
- If pool ≥ 5 and < 25: spawn 1 Tier-2 Vector at group centroid, consume all selected units.
- If pool < 5: gesture ignored, no change.
- Reinforcement: if the group contains a damaged higher-tier unit, incoming points
  heal it first (1 pt = 1 hp) before counting toward an upgrade threshold.

### Stars — power accumulation (NOT instant capture)
Stars are NOT captured instantly. Units are CONSUMED on arrival and contribute power.

| Tier transition | Power required |
|-----------------|----------------|
| 0 → 1 (capture) | 10             |
| 1 → 2           | 30             |
| 2 → 3           | 90             |
| 3 → 4           | 270            |

- `currentTier` starts at 0 (neutral, produces nothing).
- Tier 0 → 1 transition flips `ownerId` to the attacking player.
- Stars produce motes every 5 seconds when owned (currentTier ≥ 1):
  - Tier 1: 1 mote/cycle, Tier 2: 3 motes/cycle, Tier 3: 9 motes/cycle, Tier 4: 27 motes/cycle.
- Each star has a `maxTier` (set at map generation, 1–4). Power beyond maxTier is discarded.

### Mote auto-fusion
- 10 free Motes (produced by a star) auto-fuse into 1 Tier-1 Mote unit.
- No player action required. This is the idle production loop.

### Combat — unit vs unit
- Units do NOT stop to fight. They continue toward their target while combat ticks.
- Combat resolves once per second for all colliding pairs.
- Damage is simultaneous: compute BOTH damage values before writing either to state.
- Collision radii: Tier-1 = 16 px, Tier-2 = 24 px, Tier-3 = 36 px.
- Unit reaching 0 HP is removed from Flame world and Riverpod state.

### Pinch to zoom / two-finger pan
- ScaleDetector lives on AstroGame (FlameGame) — NEVER on a PositionComponent.
- `info.delta.global` and `info.scale.global` are already Vector2. No `.toVector2()`.

---

## Core mechanic — never break this
- 10 Motes fuse into 1 Tier-1 Mote unit. This ratio is fixed.
- Stars produce Motes automatically at a rate determined by their tier.
- Units are CONSUMED when they arrive at a star. Capture is never instant.
- Do not change ratios or thresholds without explicit human sign-off.

---

## Aesthetic rules — non-negotiable
- Dark background only. Never use white or light-mode colours.
- All glows must be high-saturation neon. No pastels.
- Combat and glow effects use additive blending. Use BlendMode.plus
  (BlendMode.add does NOT exist in Flutter).
- No flat Material widgets rendered inside the Flame game canvas.
- Unit colour by owner + tier:
  - Player tier 1 → cyan #00DDFF
  - Player tier 2 → mint #00FFAA
  - Player tier 3 → gold #FFDD00
  - Enemy any tier → red #FF3366
  - Neutral star   → dim white #888888

---

## Project structure
```
lib/
  game/        — FlameGame subclass (astro_game.dart) and game-loop systems
  models/      — Pure Dart data classes: Mote, Vector, Star (no Flame imports)
  components/  — Flame PositionComponents for rendering (no business logic)
  providers/   — Riverpod providers that are not the core GameStateNotifier
  systems/     — Non-Flame systems (MoteProductionSystem, PersistenceService)
```
- models/ must stay pure Dart — no Flame or Flutter imports.
- components/ depend on models/, never the reverse.

---

## Current model schema
These are the exact fields on each model. Do not invent fields that are not here.
If you add a field, you MUST update this section in the same task.

```
Mote          id: int | lifecycleState: MoteLifecycle (default: active)
              Helpers: setCreated() setActive() setFused()
              Getters: isCreated isActive isFused
              (lib/models/mote.dart)

MoteLifecycle created | active | fused

Vector        id: int | owner: String ('player'|'enemy') | tier: int (1–3)
              | currentHealth: int (default = maxHealth for tier)
              Getters: maxHealth power isAlive
              copyWith(owner, tier, currentHealth)
              (lib/models/vector.dart)

Star          id: int | tier: int (1–3) | ownerId: String ('' = neutral)
              Getters: isCaptured productionRate
              (lib/models/star.dart)

GameState     motes: List<Mote> | vectors: List<Vector> | stars: List<Star>
              (lib/models/game_state.dart)
```

Positions are NEVER stored in models. Position is a Flame/rendering concern
that lives in the component (PositionComponent.position).

---

## State management architecture
- `lib/models/game_state.dart`          — pure immutable GameState data class
- `lib/models/game_state_provider.dart` — GameStateNotifier + gameServiceProvider
- `lib/systems/persistence_service.dart` — PersistenceService + LocalPersistenceService
- Provider name: `gameServiceProvider`  (NOT `gameStateProvider`)
- Notifier type: `GameStateNotifier`
- Notifier methods (exact signatures):
  ```dart
  addMote(int id)
  addVector(int id, {String owner = 'player', int tier = 1})
  addStar(int id, int tier)
  removeMote(int id)
  removeVector(int id)
  removeStar(int id)
  updateStar(int id, int tier)
  captureStar(int id, String ownerId)
  damageVector(int id, int amount)
  spawnSurge(int id, {String owner = 'player'})
  clearMotes() clearVectors() clearStars()
  saveGame() loadGame() reset()
  ```

---

## File size
- Keep every file under 150 lines. Split into smaller focused modules if exceeded.

---

## Flutter/Flame conventions
- Prefer const constructors wherever possible.
- One class per file.
- State exposed to UI via Riverpod providers only — no direct game state reads from widgets.
- Every async operation must handle loading and error states.

---

## Vector2 vs Offset — read this before writing any component
`Vector2` and `Offset` are INCOMPATIBLE types.

- **Flame component fields** (position, size, velocity): use `Vector2`.
- **Flutter canvas draw calls**: use `Offset`.
- **Convert at the render boundary only:**
  ```dart
  // CORRECT
  canvas.drawCircle(Offset(position.x, position.y), radius, paint);
  // WRONG — compile error
  canvas.drawCircle(position, radius, paint);
  ```
- `position.toOffset()` works — use it only at canvas draw call sites.
- Never declare positional state as `Offset` inside a PositionComponent.

---

## Key API signatures — use these exactly, do not guess
```dart
// Particles — all positions are Vector2, never Offset
ParticleSystem.spawnSpark(Vector2 position, {Color? color, double? radius, Vector2? velocity, double? lifetime})
ParticleSystem.spawnRing(Vector2 position, {Color? color, double? radius, double? lifetime})
```
- `Star.ownerId` is a String (who owns it); `Star.id` is an int (identity).
- `vectorId` and `starId` are always int — never pass a String as an ID.

---

## Dart/Flame API rules — common mistakes to avoid
- BlendMode: use `BlendMode.plus`. `BlendMode.add` does NOT exist in Flutter.
- Always `import 'dart:ui';` in files using Color, Canvas, Offset, Paint, MaskFilter, BlendMode, Rect.
- PositionComponent is NOT const — never `const` its subclass constructors.
- `flame/geometry.dart` does not exist — remove it if generated.
- Canvas.drawCircle takes `(Offset, double, Paint)` — not Rect, not Vector2.
- `flame/components.dart` exports its own `Vector` type. Any file importing both
  `flame/components.dart` AND `models/vector.dart` MUST hide the Flame one:
  `import 'package:flame/components.dart' hide Vector;`
- `.withOpacity()` is deprecated — use `.withAlpha(int 0–255)`.
- `.normalized()` does not exist — use `..normalize()` (mutates) or `clone()..normalize()`.
- Mixin constraints: `on` requires a concrete class, never a type parameter.
  WRONG: `mixin Foo<T extends Component> on T`
  RIGHT: `mixin Foo on PositionComponent`
- `nova.dart` does NOT exist. The fused unit class is `Vector` in `lib/models/vector.dart`.
- `package:flame/game.dart` — ONLY import this in `lib/game/astro_game.dart` (which extends
  FlameGame) and `lib/main.dart` (which uses Flame's GameWidget). Every other file must use
  `package:flame/components.dart` instead. flame/game.dart re-exports vector_math, causing
  ambiguity wherever `models/vector.dart` is also in scope.
  WRONG (in any file other than astro_game.dart / main.dart):
    `import 'package:flame/game.dart';`
  RIGHT: `import 'package:flame/components.dart';`
- `lib/game/game_widget.dart` — do NOT import `package:flame/game.dart` here. `GameWidget`
  in that file is a plain Flutter `ConsumerWidget` wrapping a `child` with `CombatScoreWidget`
  in a Stack. Flame's GameWidget is handled in `main.dart`.
- `BitmapFont` does NOT exist in Flame. Use `TextPaint` for text rendering.
- Import paths from `lib/game/` to `lib/components/` use `'../components/...'` (one level up).
  WRONG: `import 'components/combat_score_text_component.dart';`
  RIGHT: `import '../components/combat_score_text_component.dart';`
- Do NOT write `flame.GameWidget<T, overlays: [...]>` — that is not valid Dart syntax.
  Overlays are configured via the `overlayBuilderMap` and `initialActiveOverlays` parameters.

---

## flame_audio API — exact methods only
Import: `import 'package:flame_audio/flame_audio.dart';`

| Call | What it does |
|------|-------------|
| `FlameAudio.bgm.play(filename, {double volume})` | Loop background sound |
| `FlameAudio.bgm.stop()` | Stop loop |
| `FlameAudio.play(filename, {double? volume})` | One-shot SFX |
| `FlameAudio.audioCache.loadAll([...])` | Preload assets |

Classes that do NOT exist: `SoundManager`, `SoundPlayer`, `FlameAudioPlayer`,
`AudioCache` (direct), `FlameAudio.stopAll()`, `FlameAudio.play(..., isLooping: ...)`.

`AudioService` is implemented in `lib/game/audio_service.dart` — do not rewrite it.

